---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ScrollIndicator from '../../../components/ScrollIndicator.astro';
import SplitFeature from '../../../components/sections/SplitFeature.astro';
import StatBar from '../../../components/sections/StatBar.astro';
import RelatedNav from '../../../components/sections/RelatedNav.astro';
import ProcessTimeline from '../../../components/sections/ProcessTimeline.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Virtual Power Plants (VPPs) Geelong | Earn From Your Battery | EES"
  description="Earn money from your home battery with a Virtual Power Plant. EES sets you up with the best VPP strategy for your home, not locked to any single retailer. Geelong, Surf Coast, Bellarine."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Virtual Power Plants (VPPs)</h1>
      <p>Make your battery earn money when it's not powering your home.</p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- Hero: What is a VPP, plain language -->
  <SplitFeature image="/image/photography/01_Hero_Images_OG/Frontage_18_TopCut_.webp" alt="Home battery system with VPP capability" bg="white">
    <p class="section-label">What Is a VPP</p>
    <h2>Your Battery Can Sell Power Back at $17 a Kilowatt Hour</h2>
    <p>
      A Virtual Power Plant connects your home battery to the wholesale energy market. When demand on the grid spikes and electricity prices go up, your battery automatically discharges stored energy back to the grid at those high prices. You get paid the wholesale rate, not the flat one cent feed in tariff.
    </p>
    <p>
      Here's a real example. Loy Yang coal plant in central Victoria goes down for planned maintenance. They call it in 24 hours in advance. There's going to be a shortage of electricity, so the price in the national energy market jumps to $17.50 per kilowatt hour, the maximum it can go. Your battery automatically discharges at that rate. If you've got a 16 kWh battery, that's around $272 in a two hour window.
    </p>
  </SplitFeature>


  <!-- Real earnings examples -->
  <section class="earnings-section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Real Earnings</p>
      <h2>What Our Clients Have Actually Earned</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        VPP earnings depend on market conditions, your battery size, how much charge is available, and whether you're on single or three phase power. These are real numbers from our clients.
      </p>

      <div class="earnings-grid">
        <div class="earnings-card">
          <div class="earnings-value">$170</div>
          <div class="earnings-period">per month</div>
          <p>Three phase home with a large battery, actively trading on the wholesale market. Consistent monthly returns from automated VPP trading.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="earnings-card earnings-card--highlight">
          <div class="earnings-value">$120 to $272</div>
          <div class="earnings-period">in a single 2 hour window</div>
          <p>During a grid supply shortfall when wholesale prices spiked to $17.50/kWh. The battery discharged automatically. The homeowner didn't have to do anything.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="earnings-card">
          <div class="earnings-value">3x</div>
          <div class="earnings-period">more trading power on three phase</div>
          <p>You can export 5 kW per phase. Three phase homes have 15 kW of export capacity versus 5 kW on single phase. That's three times the earning potential during price spikes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .earnings-section {
      padding: 5rem 0;
      background: #f8f9fa;
    }

    .earnings-section .section-label,
    .earnings-section h2 {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .section-intro {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0 auto 3rem;
      text-align: center;
      color: #555;
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .earnings-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 1.5rem;
      max-width: 1100px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .earnings-card {
      background: #fff;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    }

    .earnings-card--highlight {
      background: #0E2B47;
      border-color: #0E2B47;
      color: #fff;
    }

    .earnings-value {
      font-size: 2.25rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      color: #0E2B47;
      line-height: 1.1;
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }

    .earnings-card--highlight .earnings-value {
      color: #fff;
    }

    .earnings-period {
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      color: #2061B7;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .earnings-card--highlight .earnings-period {
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    }

    .earnings-card p {
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: #555;
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .earnings-card--highlight p {
      color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
    }

    @media (max-width: 800px) {
      .earnings-grid {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        max-width: 500px;
      }
    }
  </style>


  <!-- How it works -->
  <ProcessTimeline
    label="How It Works"
    heading="From Solar to Earnings"
    steps={[
      { title: 'Solar charges your battery', description: 'During the day, your solar panels generate electricity and charge your home battery as normal.' },
      { title: 'You use what you need', description: 'Your home draws from the battery first, reducing what you buy from the grid.' },
      { title: 'VPP trades automatically', description: 'When wholesale prices spike, your battery automatically exports stored energy at the market rate. You don\'t need to watch the market or make any decisions.' },
      { title: 'You earn the difference', description: 'You get paid the actual wholesale price for each kWh exported. On a good spike, that can be $17.50 per kilowatt hour versus the one cent feed in tariff.' },
      { title: 'Battery recharges tomorrow', description: 'Your solar panels refill the battery the next day and the cycle continues.' },
    ]}
  />


  <!-- Agnostic approach -->
  <SplitFeature image="/image/photography/01_Hero_Images_OG/Frontage_16_TopCut_.webp" alt="EES energy consultation" reverse bg="white">
    <p class="section-label">We're Not Locked to Any Provider</p>
    <h2>Always Looking for the Best Deal for You</h2>
    <p>
      We don't push one VPP platform or one electricity retailer. We started with Amber Energy because we thought they were the best option at the time. Now we also use Glowbird, Tango, and others depending on what makes the most sense for each client.
    </p>
    <p>
      Recently we discovered that Glowbird offers a plan where you can force charge your battery from the grid for free between 11am and 2pm. For some of our clients, especially during those three or four winter months when solar production isn't enough to fully charge the battery, this is a better strategy than Amber's wholesale pricing model.
    </p>
    <p>
      The right plan depends on your system size, your phases, your usage patterns, and the time of year. We model all of this using your actual interval data and recommend the plan that gives you the best result. If a better plan comes along next year, we'll let you know.
    </p>
  </SplitFeature>


  <!-- Winter strategy -->
  <section class="winter-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="callout-box">
        <div class="callout-accent"></div>
        <div class="callout-content">
          <h3>What happens in winter when solar isn't enough?</h3>
          <p>
            There will be two to four months of the year, typically June through August, where your solar production drops below what you need to cover your usage and fully charge the battery. This is normal.
          </p>
          <p>
            That's where the right electricity plan matters most. We can set your system to force charge the battery from the grid during off peak hours or during free periods like Glowbird's 11am to 2pm window. Your battery still gets full, your home still runs off stored energy in the evening, and you're still paying far less than a standard electricity plan.
          </p>
          <p>
            We build this winter strategy into every VPP setup. It's not an afterthought.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .winter-section {
      padding: 3rem 0;
      background: rgba(240, 238, 217, 0.25);
    }

    .winter-section .callout-box {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      display: flex;
      background: #fff;
      border-radius: 12px;
      overflow: hidden;
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    }

    .winter-section .callout-accent {
      width: 6px;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      background: #2061B7;
    }

    .winter-section .callout-content {
      padding: 2.5rem;
    }

    .winter-section .callout-content h3 {
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      color: #0E2B47;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .winter-section .callout-content p {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: #555;
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }

    .winter-section .callout-content p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      .winter-section .callout-content {
        padding: 1.5rem;
      }
    }
  </style>


  <!-- Ongoing relationship -->
  <SplitFeature image="/image/photography/01_Hero_Images_OG/Frontage_20_TopCut_.webp" alt="EES team providing ongoing energy advice" bg="light">
    <p class="section-label">Ongoing Support</p>
    <h2>Advice as a Service</h2>
    <p>
      Normal electricity retailers offer a plan for 12 months and then usually try to increase your rates. You're left comparing plans, reading fine print, and trying to work out what's actually cheapest.
    </p>
    <p>
      We take that off your plate. Because we monitor your system and know your usage, we can proactively recommend when it makes sense to switch plans. We'll reach out and say, "hey, there's a new plan that we think will work better for you," and walk you through why.
    </p>
    <p>
      It's not just install and forget. We regularly check in, update strategies, and make sure you're getting the most out of your system year after year.
    </p>
  </SplitFeature>


  <StatBar
    dark
    stats={[
      { value: '$17.50', label: 'Max wholesale price per kWh' },
      { value: '5kW', label: 'Export per phase' },
      { value: '15kW', label: 'Three phase export capacity' },
      { value: '$0', label: 'Glowbird free charge window' },
    ]}
  />


  <!-- Legal note -->
  <section class="legal-note">
    <div class="container">
      <p>
        <strong>Important:</strong> We provide general advice on electricity retailers and VPP strategies based on our experience and your system data. The final decision on which retailer to sign up with is always yours. We cannot sign up for an electricity plan on your behalf, and we recommend you review the terms of any plan before switching.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .legal-note {
      padding: 1.5rem 0;
      background: #f8f9fa;
    }

    .legal-note p {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: #888;
      line-height: 1.6;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .legal-note strong {
      color: #666;
    }
  </style>


  <RelatedNav
    heading="Part of a Bigger System"
    links={[
      { href: '/services/residential/battery-systems', title: 'Battery Storage', description: 'The battery that stores and trades your energy' },
      { href: '/services/residential/solar-systems', title: 'Solar Systems', description: 'The panels that generate the energy in the first place' },
      { href: '/services/residential/home-automation', title: 'Home Automation', description: 'Smart scheduling to maximise VPP earnings' },
      { href: '/services/faq', title: 'FAQ', description: 'Common questions about solar, batteries, and VPPs' },
    ]}
  />


  <section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <p>Want to find out how much your battery could earn?</p>
      <a href="/services/consultation" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Free Consultation</a>
      <p style="margin-top: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.95rem;">Or call us on <a href="tel:0427664827">0427 664 827</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ScrollIndicator />
</BaseLayout>
